Pietermaritzburg’s top 10 achievers for the 2021 matric class were recently gifted with R1 000 shopping vouchers each. The Liberty Midlands Mall gifted the pupils with the shopping vouchers. Among the pupils who received the R1 000 voucher at the Bessie Head Library was Kial Parmanand, Rebecca Wendy Summersgill, Morgan Alston Pearson, Thaufeeq Mohamed Patel, Sidrah Rana Qayyum, Amaan Essa, Samuel Padayachee, Usmaan Desai, Joshlon Donovan Govender, and James Robert Le Roux. The voucher handover was also attended by Msunduzi Municipality mayor, Mzimkhulu Thebolla. Meanwhile, Liberty Midlands Mall general manager, Desmond Heunis, said the pupils have shown exceptional results, adding that he hopes that they are motivated to continue learning in a way that they find fulfilling. “High school education is such an important element in ensuring that a person reaches their full potential in life,” said Heunis.